Mar 6 2008 	All Good Things Come in Small Packages	If all good things genuinely do come in small packages then Sydney House is one of them. The hotel is a charming bijou residence on an elegant road nestled between Kings Road and Fulham Road right in the heart of The Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea. The owners have renovated it to a very high standard and it is contemporary but very comfortable and very unpretentious. I stayed here for one night while on a business trip and felt very safe and relaxed. My room was bigger than I expected, expecially after reading a couple of reviews complaining the hotel was small. Yes the lift is tiny and the corridors narrow but the hotel is a converted house, if you are disabled this would be a problem but otherwise, how much time do you spend in a lift in a hotel? Personally I would prefer to relax in one of Sydney House's bright and spacious rooms which really are very well equipped with fabulous beds, a desk and chair, sofa and armchair, ample wardrobe space, bathrobes etc etc and a super shower room with powerful shower. My only complaint about the room was that there were no tea or coffee making facilites which I do like when I am away on business, if you are in the middle of writing a report you don't want to call down for room service.The reception area is small but comfortable but perhaps a little stark in decor but that is my personal taste. Breakfast was excellent, freshly squeezed pink grapefruit juice, super toast and perfect scrambled eggs, crips bacon and plum tomato. On the night I stayed I had a late meeting and went back to the hotel. Some friends called me very late and asked me to meet up with them in Annabels. I left the hotel and didn't get back until around 2am. Even before I buzzed the door the night porter opened it and asked me if I would like a nightcap or anything. To contrast this with The Ritz where I have also stayed and returned after bieng out with friends, my husband and I were left standing locked out of the hotel for several minutes until the consierge let us in. Sydney House wins hands down for comfort and service but also for being incredible value for money. I paid £145 inc tax for my room and in this location that is a real bargin. I will definately stay here again and if I stay in the summer or for longer with my husband I will book The Room at The Top which has its own private roof terrace.	
