Oct 19 2007 	Town house boutique hotel in Chelsea	Sydney House is a small boutique hotel, originally a series of row townhouses, in the Chelsea district of London. It's centrally located and quite convenient to Harrod's and Harvey Nichols (about 10 minutes away by foot), and the tube (South Kensington station) which is five minutes away. The neighborhood is quite nice with upper middle class families. We stayed in a upgraded suite on the second floor consisting of a queen/king bedroom, a small business desk, an amoire/closet, and a small bathroom with a combination tub/shower and single sink. London hotel rooms are quite small compared to many cities, and I think what we had would be considered standard. Everything was very clean and modern, and the linens were topnotch Frette. The service we received was quite good, and the staff were very helpful and friendly. There is a free internet computer in the small lobby area in addition to wireless wifi. The room rates all include breakfast in the basement restaurant/dining area, and we had our choice of fresh baked breads/croissants, muffins, yogurt, fresh fruit/juices, and pancakes. The only problem we had was the noise generated by our neighbors above us--stilleto heels make a racket on wood floors at any time of the day. Next time we're in Londong we're going to book the top floor suite so we don't hear the giraffes again. Overall we had a pretty nice stay in the hotel and would recommend it for anyone looking for a very pleasant place at a reasonable price.	
