Dec 1 2006 	The Perfect Place to Stay in Today's London	Situated in two adjacent town houses on a quiet side street in Chelsea, the Sydney House seems to me the perfect place to stay in London. You are far enough from the tourist hordes to feel a part of the real city. At the same time, the South Kensington tube station (with its direct line to/from Heathrow) is just a short walk away and then all of London is within reach. The hotel itself is stylish and smart. My partner and I have stayed in both the standard and deluxe rooms. The standard is small and the deluxe not much larger, but both are so beautifully designed as to not feel cramped. The décor is starkly modern, while the original features of the rooms have been retained. I especially like the bleached, wide-plank floors and the luxurious bedding. Someone gave much thought to the remodel of these townhouses and it all works perfectly.My one caveat for North American tourists is that this is not “jolly old England.” A stay at the Sydney House puts you in the middle of the dynamic, up to date and fully European city that London is today. And that is just where I want to be. Needless to say, we are looking forward to return visits.	
