Aug 1 2006 	Wonderful small hotel great location	My partner and I stayed at the SH for 5 nights and overall it was a great experience. As it is a townhouse, it is predictably small but clean and stylish. The beds are very comfortable and the flat screen tv (with an available dvd library) were nice touches. The rooms were small, but we expected this in London. I did not get room service or eat in the breakfast room, so I can't speak to thier quality. We were there during a heatwave and I can attest to the fact that the a/c works well. One of our favorite aspects was the location. Chelsea is lovely and though it is residential, there are a fair number of shops, bars, and restaurants in the immediate area (Kings Road is the primary location for this). Another key factor is that the hotel is a 2 min walk from the tube station that connects to 3 different lines, which is incredibly convenient. The only negative was the fact that some of the staff acted like they were doing us a favor by working there. When we arrived we were greeted by blank stares as if they were somehow shocked that (aghast) guests were actually going to interrupt whatever it is they were doing. To be fair - there were some staff members who were very helpful and pleasant. It just depended on who was working that shift. All in all though, the postives outweigh the negatives and I would reccommend the hotel. One last note...check the hotel website for discounts that could be better than anything else you'll find on the web.	
