Nov 22 2005	Many thanks to Tripadvisor	I spent hours reading reviews about hotels in London and discovered that the Sydney House was the perfect place for us. It is the kind of place that I could stay for several weeks. The accommodations were luxurious compared to some of the places we have stayed in London. The furnishings in the room as well as the public spaces were very tastefully done. The neighborhood is a little off the beaten path but in walking distance to the tube station. The shopping and restaurants in the area are upscale. All I can say is that I did not want to leave except that the prices in London are outrageous. We will definitely stay there again next time.	
Nov 19 2005 	Well Conceived	You'd be forgiven if you fail to notice the hotel at first glance. Set on a residential street a 5 minute walk from th South Kensington station, the hotel occupies 2 townhouses and blends seamlessly with the rest of the homes on Sydney street.Step inside and prepare to be surprised. The stark furnishings are more modern Scandinavian than Victorian British. Rooms are small as to be expected from hotels converted from townhouses, but the ingenious layout and minimalist decor keeps the rooms from appearing cluttered.Staff are generally friendly and helpful, especially with dining options in the area. An very pleasant and well run hotel. Will be back.	
May 31 2005	Very pleasant stay	Stayed at Sydney House for a whole week over Easter and had a lovely time. The room was on the small side but the bed was wonderful, so comfy. The only complaint was that I was woken up one night at 3am by other guests coming back to the hotel drunk. I called up the concierge and the person on duty quickly sorted it out. The staff were lovely and breakfast was good.	
May 24 2005	Sydney House - Great location good value	I just returned from a one night stay at the Sydney House. The location is perfect, both for spending time in Chelsea/South Ken (a very charming area in its own right, great for shopping and dining) and for commuting into the West End or the City via tube (Piccadilly &amp; Circle lines are a 3 minute walk away) or bus. I arrived at 9am from a transatlantic flight &amp; was immediately shown to the room, which was immaculate, very bright &amp; scandinavian in feel - all white linens and blonde wood, on the small side but it did have a king-sized bed. The front desk staff was very helpful &amp; friendly; the lobby was extremely quiet - I didn't see another guest during our entire stay, it really felt like we had the run of the place. We did hear a few people moving around in the morning, but other than that it was blissfully silent. We had a standard room overlooking the street, I was worried it would be noisy but it wasn't at all. Our bed was the most comfortable I've ever slept in anywhere in Europe (five star hotels included)...very much in the spirit of the Westin Heavenly Bed if you're familiar - lots of fluffy pillows, divinely smooth sheets. The bathroom was tiny but very modern &amp; clean, the shower had excellent pressure though the temperature was a bit finnicky. The hotel's DVD library is small but a nice touch.We paid 140 GBP for our one-night stay, which I thought was very reasonable. Highly recommended if you are looking for an intimate hotel in a perfect London neighborhood!	
Apr 23 2005 	Great night's sleep!	The bed at the Sydney House was probably my favorite feature, crisp linens, fluffy pillows, and a warm down comforter make for an excellent night's sleep. Though the rooms are typically European (small) the modern decor and extras make the room quite cozy and comfortable. Our room was at the back of the building and fairly quiet. The location is excellent, just a 2 minute walk to South Kensington tube station with plenty of restaurants and shops within walking distance. Across the street from the tube station, Carluccio's restaurant is a decent food option. The staff was quite friendly and accommodating. The only complaint was that we quite clearly heard the guest in the room directly above us pacing around his room - around midnight, and the noisy toddler in the room next door. I would however stay there again, it's a nice alternative to the larger chain hotels.	
