Feb 2 2005	Lovely but watch out for parking	I have no complaints whatsoever with the hotel itself and all the other reviews have summed it up perfectly by saying it's charming, friendly and comfortable. No-one else seems to have mentioned the flat screen TV or DVD player which I found to be extremely fun and something different to the big chains of hotel. One thing I would say is that with the warm, family atmosphere comes the problem of hearing &quot;the family&quot; coming back into their rooms at night and leaving in the morning - but this isn't really a big issue. My main problem with this hotel was the lack of reasonably priced parking in walking distance - there's one car park which costs £50 for 24 hours, which I could not believe! The rest of the parking in the vicinity is for residents, so unless you only want to park between 10pm and 7am, I'd leave these spaces well alone. All in all, a lovely place to stay, but would travel down on the train next time!	
Jan 26 2005 	Finally! A perfect little hotel in London!	What a lovely surprise! I stayed at this very discreet hotel in a posh area of London hoping for the best, but knowing that London hotels don't always live up to their expectations. A brand new, spanking clean, cool hotel in an English towntouse. Beds are firm and fluffy (4 pillows!) and tastefully decorated. The massage shower was delightful after a late night on the town! The staff was wonderful, especially the very professional manager Vojin Mandic. Breakfast in the cosy breakfast room was beautifully served complete with newspaper to read. The best thing is that it's also reasonably priced. I can only sing high praise for this hotel, and advise readers to reserve early as it's very often fully booked.	
Jan 13 2005 	Very comfortable excellent location	I have just returned from 4 nights and felt very at home here. The rooms are very comfortable with excellent beds and stylish bathrooms. The room was also immaculately clean. There are no tea &amp; coffee making facilities and I paid £7 for each cup of tea (incl. room service charge)! The room service food is not too badly priced, but the healthy options are limited, examples are fish &amp; chips, spaghetti carbonara, chilli con carne etc. The standard double rooms are pretty small but fine for one person. The location is excellent, near the best London shopping areas of the Kings Rd, Fulham Rd &amp; Knightsbridge. Most of the staff were helpful &amp; pleasant, however unfortunately the lady on reception when I checked in was very offhand and unfriendly. I expect to return here when I'm in London in the future if I can get another discounted rate online.	
